<p>This document details the classification head architecture and LoRA (Low=
-Rank Adaptation) configuration used in GigaCheck's classification model. T=
he classification head transforms the Mistral-7B backbone's hidden represen=
tations into document-level predictions (human vs. AI-generated text), whil=
e LoRA enables parameter-efficient fine-tuning of the base model.</p>
<p>For the complete model architecture including the Mistral base model, se=
e <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/5.1-mistral-base-mod=
el" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Mistr=
al Base Model</a>. For the DETR-based detection architecture, see <a href=
=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/5.3-detr-detection-architectu=
re" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">DETR =
Detection Architecture</a>.</p>
