<p>LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) is a technique that fine-tunes large language=
 models by adding trainable low-rank decomposition matrices to specific lay=
ers, rather than updating all parameters. This dramatically reduces memory =
requirements and training time while maintaining model quality.</p>
<p>GigaCheck uses LoRA exclusively for classification training, not for det=
ection training. The LoRA implementation comes from the <code class=3D"roun=
ded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[=
15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">peft</code> library =
and is applied to the Mistral base model.</p>
