<p>After merging, the resulting model:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>No adapter overhead</strong>: The LoRA matrices are integrated =
into the base weights, eliminating separate adapter computations during inf=
erence</li>
<li><strong>Simplified deployment</strong>: A single model directory instea=
d of base model + adapter files</li>
<li><strong>Compatibility</strong>: Can be loaded as a standard <code class=
=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal l=
eading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">MistralAIDet=
ectorForSequenceClassification</code> without LoRA dependencies</li>
<li><strong>Same inference performance</strong>: Produces identical outputs=
 to the unmerged model</li>
</ol>
<p>The merged model can be directly loaded for inference using the <code cl=
ass=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-norma=
l leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">MistralDe=
tector</code> class (see <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigache=
ck/6.2-mistraldetector-api" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-20=
0 hover:underline">MistralDetector API</a>) or used for further training if=
 needed.</p>
